InverseOptimalTax.title: Codecov only on `main` branch
InverseOptimalTax.body: This PR updates the GH Actions to only run `codecov` on the main branch.  This will help avoid test failures on forked repos which don't have the proper credentials to upload the codecov token.

InverseOptimalTax.title: Updates to GH Actions
InverseOptimalTax.body: This PR updates the versions of Python and other dependencies in GH Actions.  It also calls a GH Secret with the Codecov.io token to allow for uploads (previously, a token was not required on public repos).

InverseOptimalTax.title: adds pareto tails for lognormal and kde
InverseOptimalTax.body: This PR adds several methods for calculating the income distribution with a Pareto tail. These methods include a simultaneous estimate of the cutoff and pareto parameter via maximum likelihood, as well as 2 options for sequentially estimating the upper tail, with the body being estimated by lognormal or kernel density estimation.

InverseOptimalTax.title: Add another notebook with examples
InverseOptimalTax.body: This PR adds a new notebook to produce the plots use in a presentation at the National Tax Association Annual Meetings in 2023.

OG-IND.title: Use `demographics.py` from OG-Core
OG-IND.body:
This PR updates OG-IND to work well with the OG-Core versions from 0.11 and up.  This includes:

1. Using the `demographics.py` module from OG-Core
2. Accounting for the earnings ability matrix, `e` being 3-dimensional (TxSxJ)

OG-IND.title: Add `PSL_catalog.json` file
OG-IND.body: This PR adds the `PSL_catalog.json` file to be listing as PSL incubating project.

OG-IND.title: Patch to work with latest OG-Core
OG-IND.body:
This PR patches OG-IND to work with the latest OG-Core release.  

To do this, references to `surv_rate` are removed and `rho` is made into a 2-dimensional object.

Note: tests will not pass until OG-USA is updated via [this PR](https://github.com/PSLmodels/OG-USA/pull/73).

OG-IND.title: Add informal sector, update earnings ability matrix and demographics
OG-IND.body: This PR is adds the same features as in PR #17, but also adjusts the demographics files to avoid a resource constraint error in the transition path.

OG-ZAF.title: Allow download for `get_pop_objs`
OG-ZAF.body: This PR fixes an omission from PR #47, which allowed users to denote, for any function in `demographics.py` that can fetch data, whether they want to download data or look for local files.  The `download` boolean was not fully passed to all functions called in `demographics.get_pop_objs`.  This fixes that, allowing users to bypass any need for locally stored data files if they wish.
